{% comment %}
  snippets/header-utility.liquid
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  ROW 2: Utility bar — customer service links (left) + language/currency
  switcher (right).

  VARIABLES PASSED IN: none.

  GLOBALS READ DIRECTLY:
    pages[]              — resolves page URLs by handle. Each page must exist
                           in Shopify → Online Store → Pages with the matching
                           handle, or the link falls back to '#' / root_url.
    routes.root_url      — homepage fallback for Help Centre.
    localization         — current language, currency, and available languages.
                           Shopify populates this on every request.

  CALLER (sections/header.liquid):
    {% render 'header-utility' %}

  LOCALIZATION FORM NOTES:
    - {% form 'localization' %} is Shopify's official locale/currency switcher.
    - Selecting a language submits the form; Shopify handles the redirect.
    - The form id 'header-localization-form' must be unique on the page.
      If you ever render this snippet a second time (e.g. mobile drawer),
      pass a unique id_suffix variable and append it:
        id: 'header-localization-form--{{ id_suffix }}'
    - The <ul> is hidden by default; header.js toggles it open/closed.
    - aria-expanded on the trigger button is also managed by header.js.

  PAGE HANDLE MAP (update if your page handles differ):
    track-my-order  →  TRACK MY ORDER
    store-finder    →  STORE FINDER
    help-centre     →  HELP CENTRE
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
{% endcomment %}

<div class="header__utility">
  <div class="header__utility-inner page-width">

    {% comment %}
      LEFT: Customer service links.
      pages['handle'].url returns the full path if the page exists,
      blank otherwise — the | default filter catches the blank case.
    {% endcomment %}
    <nav class="header__utility-links" aria-label="Customer service">
      <a
        href="{{ pages['track-my-order'].url | default: '#' }}"
        class="header__utility-link"
      >
        TRACK MY ORDER
      </a>

      <a
        href="{{ pages['store-finder'].url | default: '#' }}"
        class="header__utility-link"
      >
        STORE FINDER
      </a>

      <a
        href="{{ pages['help-centre'].url | default: routes.root_url }}"
        class="header__utility-link"
      >
        HELP CENTRE
      </a>
    </nav>

    {% comment %}
      RIGHT: Language + currency switcher.
      Uses Shopify's {% form 'localization' %} — the only officially supported
      way to switch locale without a custom redirect handler.
      header.js handles open/close of the dropdown list.
    {% endcomment %}
    {% form 'localization', id: 'header-localization-form', class: 'header__lang-form' %}

      <button
        type="button"
        class="header__lang-switcher"
        aria-haspopup="listbox"
        aria-expanded="false"
        aria-controls="header-lang-list"
      >
        <span class="header__lang-flag" aria-hidden="true">
          {%- case localization.language.iso_code -%}
            {%- when 'en' -%}🇺🇸
            {%- when 'fr' -%}🇫🇷
            {%- when 'de' -%}🇩🇪
            {%- when 'es' -%}🇪🇸
            {%- else -%}🌐
          {%- endcase -%}
        </span>
        <span class="header__lang-label">
          {{- localization.language.name | upcase -}}
          ({{ localization.country.currency.iso_code }})
        </span>
        <span class="header__lang-caret" aria-hidden="true">▾</span>
      </button>

      <ul
        id="header-lang-list"
        class="header__lang-list"
        role="listbox"
        aria-label="Select language"
        hidden
      >
        {%- for language in localization.available_languages -%}
          {%- if language.iso_code == localization.language.iso_code -%}
            {%- assign is_active = true -%}
          {%- else -%}
            {%- assign is_active = false -%}
          {%- endif -%}

          <li role="option" aria-selected="{% if is_active %}true{% else %}false{% endif %}">
            <button
              type="submit"
              name="locale_code"
              value="{{ language.iso_code }}"
              class="header__lang-option{% if is_active %} header__lang-option--active{% endif %}"
            >
              {{- language.name -}}
            </button>
          </li>
        {%- endfor -%}
      </ul>

    {% endform %}

  </div>
</div>
